The White House has announced that applications are now open for its Summer 2018 Internship Program. The program will run from May 30 to August 10, 2018, and applicants must be at least 18 years old and U.S. citizens. They must also meet one of the following criteria: currently enrolled in an undergraduate or graduate degree program, graduated from a degree program within the past two years, or a veteran of the United States Armed Forces. The application deadline is January 12, 2018, and the program is highly competitive. Applicants will be selected based on their commitment to public service, leadership, and commitment to the Trump Administration. More information and the application can be found on the White House website.